{
  "stem": "2690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then he said, when are you leaving?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I said, yes, as soon as they tell us we can leave, we will go back to Holland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the British people came over and they said, you and your daughter can go to England right away, but not your husband because your husband is not British.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, no, I'm not going without my husband anywhere.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went through so much that I was certainly not going to England now and leave my husband alone.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We will just wait and take it as it comes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then my husband was working as a tailor for the Americans, and they wanted him to go around wherever they went because they liked his work.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was so precise and neat with everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they wanted him to go along and-- with them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After the liberation.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were still in Vittel when this happened.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then they sent us to [FRENCH], which happened to be a-- a land of Maurice Chevalier.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they put us there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not that he was good-- he was not good, either, but they-- they just took it, of course.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Like the Germans took from us, the British-- the Americans took from them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a big estate and we were there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My whole family and so many others, a lot of people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not us-- and we were not the only ones.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were a lot of Gentiles, and there was a little anti-Semitism in there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They-- they always said to me you speak much nicer than a lot of-- a lot of people had the accent, you know, that Jewish accent.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that they did not like, you know, the real English, the real, real English Gentiles.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
